         <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.1934" xml:lang="en">
            <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
            <dateline>5 Bedford Place, Croydon, Surrey, England<lb/> 28 Jan 1895</dateline>
            <opener>Dear Sir</opener>
            <p>I have not heard from you for several years, and do not know if you have published any more works on Creole dialects, especially <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.180">
                  <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Ceylon Portuguese</hi>
               </ref>. The latest I have is No. IX, Kreolische Studien. I shall be glad to receive any more you have written. I send you a paper with some <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.180">Ceylon Portuguese</ref> sentences, which may interest you. I have left Ceylon, on account of my health.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Yours truly</salute>
               <lb/>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">Donald Ferguson</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
            <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
         </div>
